# 1️⃣ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)

# 🔹 Judicial Review

Judicial Review means:

👉 Power of courts to examine laws and government actions.

If any law violates Constitution:
👉 Courts can declare it unconstitutional.

📌 Important feature of Indian Constitution.

---

## 🔵 Purpose of Judicial Review

* Protect Constitution
* Protect Fundamental Rights
* Maintain constitutional supremacy
* Control misuse of power

---

## 🔹 Constitutional Basis

Mainly derived from:

* Article 13
* Article 32
* Article 226

📌 Supreme Court and High Courts exercise this power.

---

# 🔴 Judicial Activism

Judicial Activism means:

👉 Active role played by judiciary in protecting rights and ensuring justice.

Courts sometimes give directions to government for public welfare.

---

## Examples

* Environmental protection
* Prison reforms
* Women safety
* Pollution control

📌 Judiciary becomes proactive.

---

# 🔹 Public Interest Litigation (PIL)

PIL means:

👉 Any public-spirited person can approach court for public welfare.

Started to help:

* Poor people
* Marginalized groups
* Social justice causes

---

# 🔵 Features of PIL

* Relaxed legal procedures
* Public welfare focus
* Access to justice

📌 Can even be started through letters in some cases.

---

# 🔴 Importance of PIL

* Protects rights of weak sections
* Increases access to justice
* Improves government accountability

---

# 🔹 Criticism

## Judicial Review

* Judiciary may interfere too much

## Judicial Activism

* Can lead to judicial overreach

## PIL

* Sometimes misused for publicity

---

# 🔹 Judicial Activism vs Judicial Restraint

| Judicial Activism | Judicial Restraint            |
| ----------------- | ----------------------------- |
| Active judiciary  | Limited interference          |
| Expands rights    | Respects separation of powers |

---

# 🔹 Important Facts

| Topic             | Key Point                 |
| ----------------- | ------------------------- |
| Judicial Review   | Review constitutionality  |
| PIL               | Public welfare litigation |
| Judicial Activism | Proactive judiciary       |

